sentences: Siavash Ghomayshi (Persian: سیاوش قمیشی‎; born 11 June 1945, Ahvaz) is an Iranian musician, singer and song writer.
Siavash Ghomayshi was born in Ahvaz, Iran on 11 June 1945.

Among the 17 albums Ghomayshi has recorded to date, Ragbaar, Rooz-haye Bi-Khatereh (Days with No Memories), Bi Sarzamin-tar az Baad (More Homeless Than The Wind), Taak (The Vine), and last but certainly not the least Yadegari ("Memento") (2011) have been among his most successful.

Ghomayshi has also had significant involvement in albums released by various musical compatriots, "The Story of Yours, The Story of Mine", "Setarehaye Sorbi (1995) and Shab-e-Niloufari (2003)", which attracted a lot of attention with great reviews.

In 2011 in an interview with teamghomayshi.com he stated that Yadegari ("Memento") (2011) would most probably be his last album, However, till present day, his last album is "Sargozasht (2017)" that contains 9 songs; but to let his fans enjoy his music and his unique style, he will be releasing singles.

Over the past four decades, he composed songs for artists like Ebi, Moein, Aref, Mansour, Leila Forouhar, Shohreh Solati and others.
He left Iran in 1978 and now lives in Los Angeles.
Ghomayshi wrote his first song, called "Ghayeghran" ("Boatman") for Zia when he was only 13 old years.
Although initially considered a composer, in the latter years he released his first single "Farangis", and has since continued his work as a singer, composer, arranger, and lyricist.
In recent years Siavash Ghomayshi has explored electronic music as well such experimentation has introduced new elements into his music and the whole Iranian pop music.

Among the 17 albums Ghomayshi has recorded to date, Ragbaar, Rooz-haye Bi-Khatereh (Days with No Memories), Bi Sarzamin-tar az Baad (More Homeless Than The Wind), Taak (The Vine), and last but certainly not the least Yadegari ("Memento") (2011) have been among his most successful.
Because of the popularity of Siavash's voice among young generation, in recent years many singers have followed his style.
